President Biden spoke with Acting FEMA Administrator Bob Fenton regarding the severe winter weather situation in central and southern parts of the United States. The President expressed his support for FEMA's efforts in providing aid such as generators, water, blankets, and ongoing support to the affected areas. He also thanked FEMA for their role in responding to the COVID-19 pandemic and assisting with vaccination deployment. President Biden assured Acting Administrator Fenton that he was prepared to mobilize other federal agencies to provide additional support to Texas and meet any critical needs. He also stated his intention to sign Texas's request for a Major Disaster Declaration once it is received from Governor Abbott. The President stated that the White House would remain in close contact with FEMA, local officials, and relief organizations to monitor the impact of the storms as they progress.